Bayer May Shift Production From Germany on Energy, Wiwo Says

-- B y   B r i a n   P a r k i n
-- 
2011-08-06T13:59:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-06/bayer-may-shift-production-from-germany-on-energy-wiwo-says.html
Bayer AG (BAYN)  may relocate some production
facilities away from Germany to cut energy costs, the company’s
Management Board Chairman Marijn Dekkers said in an interview in
the  Wirtschaftswoche  weekly.  “As a production location, Germany is becoming more
unattractive for the energy-intensive  chemical industry ,”
Dekkers is cited as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Parkin in Berlin at 
 bparkin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  